4. If 1. 38 has a fitness at the end of a Book, we may note a similar fitness for their place in 2. 20 and 3. 1. The adaptation indeed of these two Odes to their position was doubtless what sug- gested the now abandoned theory of a separate publication of Books i, ii, and Book iii. That theory can really derive no support from them, for it would necessitate, as we have seen, an entire rearrange- ment of the Odes in a chronological order, in the course of which all evidence would disappear of the position of these two Odes as well as of all the others.
